image.altText: Voyager of Australia performs during dress rehearsals for the Grand final at the Eurovision Song Contest

items.synopsis: After two rounds of semis, 26 countries are facing off in Liverpool, UK, to be crowned the winner of Eurovision 2023.

title.children: Australia's Voyager steal the show at the 2023 Eurovision grand final

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Finally, they're here! After the best part of a decade of trying, Voyager become the first band to represent Australia at Eurovision. Has it been worth waiting for? You bet. Voyager are a Perth-based synth-metal — or progressive metal — group, putting just as much emphasis on melody as the heavy elements of their music. Crucially for Australia's chances, they are epic live performers - and you only wish you could bottle the energy they have brought to their semi-final and the all-important jury final this time yesterday. The song and their performance saw them roar through their semi-final earlier this week thanks to strong public support. Now they have to convince Europe to vote for them again. LYRICS: I'm here tonight Promise mе you'll hold me 'til I die I'm by your side Promisе me it's gonna Promise me it's gonna be alright Watch out for the epic breakdown halfway through, the general showmanship of the entire crew led by frontman Danny Estrin, and the big finish which should have the Liverpool Arena absolutely jumping.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 15: Australia - Voyager, Promise

props.alt: Voyager lead singer Danny Estrin performs for Australia in rehearsals for the Eurovision Song Contest

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: AUSTRIA WERE AMAZING! here are some of my other faves for the contest Czechia – My Sister's Crown by Vesna: You want girl power? All-female sextet Vesna's got it for you — their entry into the competition is all but a battled cry against gender inequality set against a hybrid backdrop of power-pop and Slavic folk. Austria - Who the hell is Edgar? by Teya & Salena: Besides being an absolute What Does The Fox Say-esq bop, it has hands down the best music video in the comp Finland – Cha Cha Cha by Käärijä: Show me someone who doesn't get this stuck in their head and I'll show you a liar. If it wasn't for the weird breakdown at the end this would be one of my top tops. Israel – Unicorn by Noa Kirel : Another fierce track, it was co-written by one of the people on Netta's 2018 winner toy which has always held a soft spot in my heart. Australia - Promise by Voyager : Self-explanatory. This song rules. Voyager forever.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Velvet's top five
